<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD>
<H3><BR>
<A NAME="What is"></A>What is HivNet.ch?</H3>

<UL>
<LI>HivNet.ch is the Swiss electronic information and exchange service
about HIV and AIDS, created by the <I>Fondation du Pr&eacute;sent</I>,
(Gen&egrave;ve)<BR>
</LI>
<P>
<LI>HivNet.ch is the distrubution relay on the Internet for the <I>Fondation
Sida Info Doc Suisse</I> (Berne)<BR>
</LI>
<P>
<LI>HivNet.ch is the Swiss Internet site dedicated to organizations in the fight
against HIV and AIDS</LI>
<P>
<LI>HivNet.ch is a free service associated with the European HIV and AIDS
information network <A HREF="http://www.hivnet.org/">HIVNET</A>. </LI>

</UL>

<H3><A NAME="Who uses"></A>Who uses HivNet.ch?</H3>

<UL>
<P>HivNet.ch is a place of dialogue and solidarity open to all - to people
concerned about their health or the health of others; people who are HIV
positive or have AIDS, as well as their families and loved-ones; medical
researchers and doctors - anyone who would like to stay informed on the
progress in the fight against AIDS...<I>and you always have the choice
to retrieve information from HivNet.ch anonymously</I></P>
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="How can I"></A>How can I benefit from HivNet.ch?</H3>

<UL>
<P>HivNet.ch allows your group or organization:</P>

<LI>to publish your information on the World Wide Web</LI>

<LI>to develop your Internet projects <I>free</I></LI>

<LI>to create E-mail distribution lists to keep your members informed of
the latest news, both in Switzerland and around the world</LI>

<LI>to make your databases and libraries accessible to the public</LI>

<LI>to create new forums for anonymous advice and information for your
members and the public at large</LI>

<LI>to prepare yourselves to actively participate in national and international
conferences on HIV/AIDS</LI>

<LI>to obtain personal E-mail addresses for you and your members</LI>
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="How do I access"></A>How do I access HivNet.ch?</H3>

<UL>
<P>Access to HivNet.ch is free. If you would like to take advantage of
our services, please fill out the <A HREF="/e/info/form6E.html"><B>Participation Form</B></A></P>
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="Who supports"></A>Who supports HivNet.ch?</H3>

<UL>
<P>HivNet.ch is supported by the <I>Fondation Sida Info Doc Suisse </I>(Berne),
and the <I>Office F&eacute;d&eacute;ral de la sant&eacute; publique</I>
(Swiss Ministry of Health, Berne) and the State of Gen&egrave;ve. </P>

<P>HivNet.ch also benefits from the generous support of the following organizations
and institutions below:</P>
</UL>

<UL>
<LI><I>Aide Suisse contre le Sida</I> (ASS) </LI>

<LI><I>Centre Hospitalier Universitaire Vaudois, Division des maladies
infectieuses</I> </LI>

<LI>Global Network of People living with HIV/AIDS </LI>

<LI><I>Groupe Sida Gen&egrave;ve</I> </LI>

<LI><I>H&ocirc;pital Cantonal Universitaire de Gen&egrave;ve, Division
des maladies infectieuses</I> </LI>

<LI><I>H&ocirc;pital Universitaire de Zurich, Division des Maladies Infectieuses
</I></LI>

<LI><I>Loterie romande </I></LI>

<LI>People With AIDS Switzerland </LI>

<LI><I>Personnes Vivant Avec (PVA Gen&egrave;ve)</I> </LI>

<LI>SUN Microsystems (Gland) </LI>

<LI><I>Universit&eacute; de Fribourg, D&eacute;partement de Psychologie</I>
</LI>

<LI><I>Universit&eacute; de Gen&egrave;ve, Services Informatiques</I></LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<UL>
<UL>
<P>
