<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>EnviroWorld: VOTE for the Person of the Year!</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../Images/backgrdgrn.gif">

<P><IMG SRC="../Images/EWlogobig.gif" WIDTH="112" HEIGHT="28" ALIGN="BOTTOM"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"> <FONT COLOR="#006600" SIZE=+4>1996 Person of the Year
Award</FONT></P>

<UL>
  <UL>
    <UL>
      <DL>
        <DD><FONT COLOR="#663300" SIZE=+2>Who will follow in the steps of Archie
        Carr, Carol Browner, Nat Reed, Dexter Lehtinen, Virginia Wetherell, Pam
        McVety, Marjorie Stoneman Douglas, Margaret Hames, and Tom Pelham?</FONT>
        <DD>&nbsp;
        <DD><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#006600" SIZE=+1>Who best exemplifies
        the award's appreciation for:</FONT>
        <DD><P ALIGN=CENTER><I><FONT COLOR="#006600" SIZE=+2>&quot;A lifetime of
        work and dedication of Florida's environment.&quot;</FONT></I>
        <DD>&nbsp;
        <DD><FONT SIZE=+1>This year's slate of nominees has been selected from
        the field of candidates submitted by the readers of <I>Florida Environments</I>
        magazine and <I>EnviroWorld Daily News Service</I>. The nominees are:</FONT>
        <DD>&nbsp;
      </DL>
      <UL>
        <LI><A HREF="mailto:info@enviroworld.com">Mary Barley</A>, who led the
        drive to pass three constitutional amendments aimed at funding and implementing
        the cleanup of the Florida Everglades.
      </UL>
    </UL>
  </UL>
</UL>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<UL>
  <UL>
    <UL>
      <UL>
        <LI><A HREF="mailto:info@enviroworld.com">Carol Browner</A>, the Florida
        native and former DEP secretary who now leads the U.S. EPA. Browner won
        the award in 1993.
      </UL>
    </UL>
  </UL>
</UL>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<UL>
  <UL>
    <UL>
      <UL>
        <LI><A HREF="mailto:info@enviroworld.com">Tom Reese</A>, the environmental
        attorney who led the successful opposition to the proposed new power plants
        in Manatee County that would have burned the controversial fuel called
        Orimulsion.
      </UL>
    </UL>
  </UL>
</UL>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<UL>
  <UL>
    <UL>
      <UL>
        <LI><A HREF="mailto:info@enviroworld.com">Marjorie Carr</A>, the leader
        of Florida Defenders of the Environment whoa has championed the restoration
        of habitats destroyed by the Cross Florida Barge Canal. Carr's late husband,
        Archie, was the first recipient of this award in 1986.
      </UL>
      <DL>
        <DD>&nbsp;
        <DD><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">VOTE</FONT></B> here by selecting your choice
        and sending in an e-mail with that name in it. The winner will be announced
        March 1st.
        <DD>&nbsp;
        <DD><FONT COLOR="#FF0000" SIZE=+4>VOTE NOW!</FONT>
      </DL>
    </UL>
  </UL>
</UL>
