<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<P><A HREF="../index.html">Return to Cover Page</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../Images/sebc.gif" WIDTH="130" HEIGHT="33" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
The Southern Environmental Business Council</P>

<H3><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor324429">What Is The Southern Environmental
Business Council?</A><A NAME="anchor324429"></A></H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>The Southern Environmental Business Council (SEBC) is an association
  of firms that provide environmental products and services. The SEBC is
  modeled after state and regional environmental business councils in 15
  states. The membership of the SEBC includes equipment manufacturers, engineering
  and consulting firms, solid and hazardous waste management companies, remedial
  and emergency response contractors, professional services, analytical testing
  laboratories, investment firms, and lending, financial, and educational
  institutions, representing a vital new growth industry. <BR>
  The SEBC and its Board of Directors believe there are business opportunities
  in restoring and protecting the environment. Therefore, the SEBC is committed
  to helping the environmental industry promote its interests and deal more
  effectively with governments, here and abroad. <BR>
  </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor325514">Mission Statement</A><A NAME=
"anchor325514"></A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>&quot;Working for a sustainable future.&quot;</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>The mission of the Southern Environmental Business Council is to advance
  the competitiveness and growth of the environmental industry by helping
  members build partnerships in the marketplace in order to achieve a clean,
  produtive, and sustainable environment.</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;</H3>

<H3><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor324585">What Kinds of Programs Does The
SEBC Sponsor?</A><A NAME="anchor324585"></A></H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>- Seminars on regulatory developments, financing growth, marketing,
  exporting, and other business development issues.<BR>
  - A directory containing information on environmental companies, including
  contract information and a company description.<BR>
  - Joint education and training programs with academic and non-profit institutions.<BR>
  - A means to foster the development and implementation of sound environmental
  policies by reviewing and commenting on state and federal legislation and
  regulations. <BR>
  </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>For more information call 1-813-725-8208<BR>
<HR></H3>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="mailto:sebc@enviroworld.com">How to join</A><HR></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../index.html">Return to Cover Page</A></H3>
