<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../Images/RFT.gif" WIDTH="256" HEIGHT="189" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" BORDER="1"></P>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#anchor1518684">RecycleFlorida Today, Inc.</A>
<BR>
(RFT)<A NAME="anchor1518684"></A></H1>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>The RFT Home Page</I></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="anchor1624732"></A><BR>
An Association Dedicated to Promoting <BR>
Successful Recycling in the State of Florida<BR>
<HR SIZE="9"></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <UL>
    <LI><A HREF="#anchor1523187">Mission</A>
    <LI><A HREF="#anchor1642812">Activities</A>
    <LI><A HREF="#anchor1552268">Services</A>
    <LI><A HREF="#anchor1560241">Get Involved</A>
    <LI><A HREF="#anchor1599618">Links to other sources of Recycling information</A>
    <BR>
    
  </UL>
  <P ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="anchor1523187"></A></P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor1624732">Return to topics</A> | <A HREF=
"../index.html">Return to EnviroWorld</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H2><A HREF="#anchor1523187">Mission</A></H2>

<P><BR>
<B><I>The purpose of RecycleFlorida Today, Inc. (RFT) is: </I></B></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>&middot; To function as a professional association among individuals
        engaged in the business of recycling.<BR>
        <BR>
        &middot; To assist individual members in improving skills and techniques
        in recycling. This will be achieved through education, special studies,
        research, and the exchange of ideas and technical knowledge related to
        all forms of recycling.<BR>
        <BR>
        &middot; To provide a forum for public, private and non-profit recyclers
        to mutually discuss and resolve recycling issues.<BR>
        <BR>
        &middot; To inform the public, law-making bodies and the business community
        of the economic significance and importance of recycling, and to demonstrate
        the high professional standards of those involved in the business of recycling.
        This will be accomplished through sponsorship of educational meetings,
        research and publication of articles, reports, statistics, and other <BR>
        material.<BR>
        <BR>
        &middot; To lobby for legislation that promotes recycling.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><BR>
<A NAME="anchor1642812"></A><BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor1624732">Return to topics</A> | <A HREF=
"../index.html">Return to EnviroWorl</A><A HREF="stateEPresorces.html">d
</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H2><A HREF="#anchor1642812">Activities</A></H2>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><B><I><BR>
  RFT activities are intended to bring together recycling professionals on
  state and national levels.</I></B></P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P>Meetings/Conferences</P>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>The National Recycling Congress (NRC) is held in the fall of each
        year. This conference is an opportunity for local professionals to gain
        a national perspective. Multiple tracks are offered to accommodate all
        <BR>
        areas of industry and all levels of experience.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  RFT Annual Membership Meeting/Conference</P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>The RFT Annual Membership Meeting/Conference is held in the spring
        of each year. Emphasis is placed on issues that face Florida as a state
        and the southeast as a region. The annual business meeting includes progress
        reports, election of Board of Directors and general business issues. The
        conference also provides networking opportunities for both the public and
        private sectors.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  Issue Forums</P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>Issue Forums are held biannually, one prior to the legislative session
        to discuss views on pending legislation, and one typically towards the
        fall to facilitate the exchange of ideas and technical <BR>
        knowledge related to all forms of recycling.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>Committee Meeting/Workshops &amp; Conferences</P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>In order to meet the needs of the membership, committee meetings/workshops
        and other conferences are scheduled on a periodical basis throughout the
        year.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <BR>
  <A NAME="anchor1552268"></A></P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor1624732">Return to topics</A> | <A HREF=
"../index.html">Return to EnviroWorld</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H2><A HREF="#anchor1552268">Services</A></H2>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <B><I>RFT provides many services to its members including:</I></B></P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P>The NRC Connection</P>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>The NRC Connection is a monthly newsletter Developed and distributed
        by the NRC to all RFT Members. It includes topics of national interest.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P>Renewable News</P>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>Published quarterly, Renewable News is designed to assist the membership
        of RFT. The focus is on a state level and includes such information as:
        market trends, legislative reports, membership news, <BR>
        and upcoming meetings and conference dates.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P>Legislative Alerts</P>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P><B>Members are provided information as new bills or language changes
        are introduced which have the potential to affect the recycling community.</B></P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <BR>
  <BR>
  <A NAME="anchor1560241"></A></P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="#anchor1624732">Return to topics</A> | <A HREF=
"../index.html">Return to EnviroWorld</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

