      <BR>
      newsletter Renewable News and promoting the annual conference. <BR>
      Additionally, the committee is planning to become proactive in promoting
      <BR>
      RecycleFlorida Today to the recycling trade and in providing more <BR>
      information to the RFT membership.</P>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <SELECT>
  <OPTION SELECTED>yes
  <OPTION>no
  <OPTION>maybe later
  </SELECT>Membership Committee</P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <P>The Membership Committee has several responsibilities, including working
      <BR>
      to retain membership as well as recruit new members, develop a <BR>
      membership directory, and conduct a survey of RFT member needs.</P>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <SELECT>
  <OPTION SELECTED>yes
  <OPTION>no
  <OPTION>maybe later
  </SELECT>Education Committee</P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <P>The Education Committee is responsible for putting together the tow
      issues <BR>
      Forums held each year. This includes developing topics of current and <BR>
      timely interests to the membership and securing speakers and sponsors.
      The <BR>
      committee will also work to foster relationships and co-sponsorships with
      <BR>
      other recycling oriented groups (e.g., Advance Recycling Coordinators'
      <BR>
      Training). This committee will also work with the membership to develop
      <BR>
      articles for publication in national and local periodicals.</P>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <SELECT>
  <OPTION SELECTED>yes
  <OPTION>no
  <OPTION>maybe later
  </SELECT>Conference Committee</P>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <P><BR>
      The Conference Committee is responsible for all aspects of planning the
      <BR>
      annual conference-program and speaker selection, location, events, socials,
      <BR>
      exhibitions, sponsorships, entertainment - you name it , they do it.</P>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><BR>
  <B><I>For additional information contact:<BR>
  </I></B></P>
