ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></P>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Tanks cleanup work payments speeding up</H1>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><I>December 12, 1996</I></P>

<UL>
  <UL>
    <UL>
      <DL>
        <DD><FONT SIZE=-1>by Dave Newport, Editor</FONT>
        <DD>&nbsp;
        <DD><IMG SRC="../Images/tanks.gif" WIDTH="144" HEIGHT="103" ALIGN="LEFT"
        NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"><FONT SIZE=+4>A </FONT>NEW SYSTEM designed
        to insure a fair price and timely payment for the cleanup of leaking underground
        petroleum tanks seems to be speeding up the work--and the payments.
      </DL>
    </UL>
  </UL>
</UL>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
      <BLOCKQUOTE>
        <P>Florida Department of Environmental Protection tanks cleanup program
        chief Mike Sole last month unveiled figures sure to brighten up the dark
        moods of tanks cleanup contractors hard hit by an industry-wide slowdown
        and the demise of Florida's old tanks cleanup program.<BR>
        </P>
      </BLOCKQUOTE>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><TABLE WIDTH="416" HEIGHT="200" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING=
  "0">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="40%">  <FONT SIZE=+1>&nbsp;</FONT><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000" SIZE=+1>&quot;I firmly
  believe that the [preapproval] process is working,&quot; said Sole. &quot;We
  need to keep making it better, but we're on the right path.&quot;</FONT></B></TD>
<TD WIDTH="60%" VALIGN="TOP">  <P>&nbsp;Compared to a March 1996 total tanks preapproval expenditure of
  just over $500,000, seven months later DEP had issued nearly $8 million
  in new work orders.</P>

  
  <P>&quot;I firmly believe that the [preapproval] process is working,&quot;
  said Sole. &quot;We need to keep making it better, but we're on the right
  path.&quot;</P>

  
  <P>The preapproval system was mandated by the 1995 Florida Legislature
  after a perception that DEP was mismanaging and cleanup contractors were
  abusing the work-now, get paid later reimbursement system used in the early
  1990s.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
