<HTML><HEAD>  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">  <TITLE></TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><P><A HREF="../CoverPages/news.html">return to Daily News Cover Page</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P><H2 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../Images/EWlogobig.gif" WIDTH="353" HEIGHT="104" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></H2><H1 ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="anchor795408"></A>Business News</H1><P ALIGN=CENTER>--Updated January 9, 1997--</P><H1 ALIGN=CENTER><HR><IMG SRC="../Images/image98.gif" WIDTH="288" HEIGHT="72" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></H1><H2><HR ALIGN=LEFT>Awards</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>The Kennedy Space Center has received the 1996 Federal Energy and  Water </B>Management Award.  This award recognizes KSC's efforts to promote  a cleaner environment and save taxpayer dollars by conserving energy.   In fiscal year 1995, KSC avoided more than $1 million in energy costs.   Kennedy's Base Operations Contractor, EG&amp;G Florida, Inc., contributed  to that savings by implementing more than 13 energy conservation projects  through their Energy Management Office.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Office Openings</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Live Oak Consulting Group, Inc. recently began providing ecological  consulting </B>services in Florida.  Based in Riverview, near Tampa, Live  Oak Consulting is run by Dorie Faulkner, a Florida ecologist with 20 years  of environmental experience.  The new office is located at 7407 U.S. Highway  301 South, Suite 100.  The phone number is 813-677-1811.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Projects</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>ECOS Capital (&quot;ECI&quot;), a subsidiary of ECOS Group, Inc.,  has signed a joint venture </B>agreement with National RE/Sources, LLC,  a Connecticut-based private real estate development company devoted to  the acquisition of environmentally impaired assets.  Under the agreement,  ECI will share in the profits of brownfields properties that it performs  remedial services on or contributes equity to.  The remedial services will  be provided by ECI's sister companies Evans Environmental &amp; Geological  Science and Management Inc. and American Remedial Technologies, Inc.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Office Expansions</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Louis Berger &amp; Associates Inc. has signed a two-year lease on  a 2,070-square-foot </B>office in the Winter Park Business Center.  The  international engineering firm has been in Florida for two years and has  relocated from its offices on Lee Road in Winter Park.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Contracts</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Environmental Assessments and Consulting, Inc. has been awarded a  three-year </B>asbestos consulting services contract by the City of Sarasota.   EAC will consult with the City of Sarasota on all asbestos projects relating  to right-of-way acquisition, asbestos project management and real property  acquisition.</P>  <P>&nbsp;</P>  <P><B>The Orlando office of Law Engineering &amp; Environmental Services,  Inc. has been </B>awarded a $275,000 contract by Orange County to provide  lead and asbestos consulting services for the historic Orange County Courthouse  in downtown Orlando.  Law's services will include asbestos and lead inspection,  asbestos and lead abatement design and project monitoring for the renovation  of the courthouse building, and demolition of the 10-story annex and 12-story  tower.  The projected budget for the abatement is $1.5 million.  Law's  inspection services were scheduled to be completed by the end of December  and the abatement project is expected to be completed by October 1997.</P>  <P>&nbsp;</P>  <P><B>The West Coast Regional Water Supply Authority in Clearwater has  named Parsons </B>Brinkerhoff as representive for the development of a  seawater desalinization plant to be built in the Tampa are.  The new plant  will be located in southern Pasco, Pinellas or Hillsborough county and  will tie in with existing or extended water supply lines of the WCRWSA.   It will provide between 20 and 50 mgd of additional water supply for Pinellas  County.  </P>  <P>PB will prepare a Request for Qualifications and Request for Proposals  for the Authority and will assist in the bidder qualification and selection  process.  PB will also undertake evaluations of all submittals to help  determine the most advantageous process for the desalinization plant.   During this period, a significant public information and community involvement  program will be initiated. </P>  <P>&nbsp;</P>  <P><B>The U.S. Army Garrison, Aberdeen Proving Ground, Maryland, announced  that it has </B>offered a five-year Base Environmental Support Contract  valued at $100 million to Roy F. Weston, Inc.  Under the contract, Weston,  an environmental services firm, will be responsible for various environmental  compliance and restoration activities at Aberdeen Proving Ground.<BR>  </P></BLOCKQUOTE><P><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../CoverPages/news.html">Return to Daily News CoverPage</A> | <A HREF="#anchor795408">Florida Headlines</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></BODY></HTML>
