 and methods for quantitatively estimating community  level risks from single or multiple chemicals.  These evaluations include  measures of uncertainty and can be applied to existing or future situations.   Such risk assessments can be used by Water &amp; Air Research for permitting  effluent discharges and to evaluate hazardous waste site impacts.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Johnston joins enviro firm in Bradenton</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Ed Barber &amp; Associates, an environmental management and consulting  services firm </B>located in Bradenton, has added one more employee.  Sam  Johnston, Jr. has joined the firm as associate.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Engineer attends HazWaste Conference</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Dr. Jerry Steinberg, P.E., senior staff engineer of Water &amp; Air  Research, Inc. recently </B>chaired a session on Groundwater Remediation  Issues for the HazWaste Conference.  The conference was held as part of  the HazWaste World Superfund XVII.  W.A.S.T.E. '96 in Washington, D.C.  on Oct. 14-17.  Steinberg has been President of the Hazardous Materials  Control Research Institute since 1987 and has served as an officer on the  ASCE National Committee for Management of Hazardous and Solid Waste for  several years.  He has extensive experience in hazardous waste management.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Smith gets appointed to historic society </H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>David J. Smith, president of R.C. Stevens Construction Co., in Orlando,  has been </B>appointed to the Board of Directors for the Orange County  Historical Society, Inc.  Founded in 1926, R.C. Stevens Construction provides  a full-service general contractor and construction management.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>Arvay joins ERM as GIS/CADD Technician</H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Matthew B. Arvay joins Environmental Resources Management as a Geographic  </B>Information System/Computer Aided Design Drafting technician.  He has  more than four years experience working in the public and private sectors  developing, defining and managing geographic information systems.  Arvay's  expertise includes client demonstrations, technical support and database  management design.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><H2>CCI Environmental hires Richardson </H2><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B>Sherry Richardson has joined CCI Environmental Services, Inc. as  director of </B>business development.  She has more than 17 years of marketing  and client relations  experience.  In her new position, Richardson will  be responsible for client relations, public relations and busienss development  activities.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P><BR><BR><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../CoverPages/news.html"><B>Return to Daily NewsCover Page</B></A></BODY></HTML>
