<P><CENTER>Welcome to </CENTER>
<H1><CENTER>EnviroWorld's 'Circulation in the Sunshine'</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER>Courtesy of <BR>
<IMG SRC="../Images/netbutt.gif" WIDTH="80" HEIGHT="96" ALIGN="BOTTOM" 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<A NAME="anchor1952210"></A></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER><HR></CENTER>
</H2>
<H2><A HREF="#anchor1952210">EnviroWorld visitors verification</A></H2>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H4>Visitor Counters are of limited use</H4>
<BR>
Every site (including ours until recently) has a visitor counter on the
front page. &quot;Welcome, you are visitor number so-and-so,&quot; they
claim. But such counters are woefully inaccurate. For instance, many regular
site visitors bookmark past the front page and are never recorded. And the
counters tell little about who is visiting the site, what they look at,
how long they stay, and so forth. And some unscrupulous site operators simply
fiddle with the numbers.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H4>A better way</H4>
We believe we have a good site--and we know that people are using it. So
we have contracted with <B><A HREF="http://www.netcount.com/">NetCount</A></B>,
an independant third-party auditing firm, to provide site-use demographics
for our advertisers. NetCount's software operates independently of ours,
measuring and evaluating each and every visitor that arrives in EnviroWorld.
All the data is then crunched by their statistical package and presented
in a useful format. <BR>
<BR>
PLEASE NOTE <A HREF="netcount_priva.html">PRIVACY STATEMENT</A>: We do not
capture or retain site visitors' names or addresses. NetCount's business
depends on its credibility. So they keep the data on their server, not ours.
We are allowed access to it--and you can look at it too.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H4>Let the Sun shine in</H4>
We have developed a policy that allows anybody to look at any of the circulation
data they so desire. First, for general site use statistics, we'll post
<A HREF="netcount_stats.html">weekly summaries</A> here. For more detailed
information, <A HREF="mailto:info@enviroworld.com">simply e-mail in your
request</A>, and you will be given the demographics you desire. It's that
easy--and open.</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
