<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY LINK="#00fd00" BGCOLOR="#ccf5cc">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Images/feaa.gif" WIDTH="258" HEIGHT="101" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"></CENTER>
<H3><CENTER>Florida Environmental Assessors <BR>
Association, Inc. (FEAA)</CENTER>
</H3>
<B><BR>
</B><HR>
<H1><CENTER>Certification</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER>The FEAA in conjunction with the University of Florida TREEO
Center provides a certification program designed to assure that professionals
providing Phase I ESAs have an acceptable academic background and a minimal
level of appropriate experience.<BR>
<BR>
Those who complete the program are issued a certificate from TREEO, FEAA,
and National Registry of Environmental Professionals (NREP).<BR>
<BR>
CFEAs (Certified Florida Environmental Assessor) are required to complete
certification maintenance every two years. To qualify, individuals must
have accumulated additional hours of professional development credit during
the preceding two-year period. These credits may be satisfied by a combination
of related work experience, attendance at approved seminars and courses,
professional publications, participation on professional boards and relevant
public service activities.</CENTER>
<P><HR>More Information<BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor363054"><B>ACADEMIC TRAINING/DEGREE</B></A><BR>
<B><A HREF="#anchor361447">CERTIFICATION EXAM</A></B><BR>
<B><A HREF="#anchor361599">PROFESSIONAL CERTIFICATION<BR>
</A><A HREF="#anchor360763">MAINTENANCE OF CERTIFICATION</A></B></CENTER>
<P><HR><BR>
<P><CENTER><B>CERTIFIED FLORIDA ENVIRONMENTAL ASSESSOR (CFEA)<BR>
STANDARDS - QUALIFICATIONS - EDUCATION</B></CENTER>
<P><A NAME="anchor363054"></A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="#anchor363054">1.0 ACADEMIC TRAINING/DEGREE</A></B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>1.1 The FEAA will recognize academic degrees, from accredited
institutions, in the following disciplines:
<BLOCKQUOTE>A. Architecture and Engineering
<BLOCKQUOTE>Environmental<BR>
Chemical<BR>
Geotechnical<BR>
Civil<BR>
Mechanical</BLOCKQUOTE>
B. Natural Sciences
<BLOCKQUOTE>Geography<BR>
Geology/Hydrogeology<BR>
Hydrology<BR>
Physics<BR>
Chemistry/Geochemistry<BR>
Biology<BR>
Soils<BR>
Environmental &amp; Occupational Health<BR>
Environmental Science</BLOCKQUOTE>
C. Law
<BLOCKQUOTE>Environmental</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>D. Social and Behavioral Sciences 
<BLOCKQUOTE>Urban and Regional Planning <BR>
Resource Management</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
1.2 The FEAA will recognize other area(s) of engineering and/or scientific
study found to be acceptable to the <A NAME="anchor361447"></A>FEAA/SQ&amp;E
application review committee/board.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR><A HREF="#anchor361447"><B>2.0</B> <B>CERTIFICATION EXAM</B></A><BR>
<P><CENTER>Candidates, for certification by the National Registry of Environmental
Professionals (NREP), will be required to take and successfully complete
an examination which will cover the following basic areas:</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>2.1 Applicable Federal and State of Florida laws and regulations.<BR>
2.2 Basic Assessment methods.<BR>
2.3 Basics of environmental chemistry, hydrogeology, toxicology, remediation
methods, assessment, monitoring, sampling and analysis, and health and safety
as it applies to site inspection.<BR>
2.4 Ethical and legal considerations for the consultant.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><CENTER>The certification exam will consist of two parts. Part I of the
exam will be the basic exam given by the National Registry of Environmental
Professionals (NREP) for certification as a Registered Environmental Property
Assessor (REPA). Part II of the exam will consist of Florida specific questions
related to the conduct of Phase I ESAs. Those individuals already holding
REPA certification by NREP will only be required to take the second part
of the test dealing with state specific subject matters. The exam will be
administered and graded by NREP.</CENTER>
<P><A NAME="anchor361599"></A><BR>
<HR><A HREF="#anchor361599"><B>3.0</B> <B>PROFESSIONAL CERTIFICATION</B></A><BR>
<P><CENTER>Presently, FEAA will only focus on that area of professional
practice related to the conduct of Phase I Environmental Site Assessments.</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>3.1 Certified Florida Environmental Assessor (CFEA).<BR>
3.1.1 The minimum required experience for 3.1, above, is three (3) years
relevant environmental and/or engineering work related to ESAs.<BR>
3.1.2 Experience credit will be given for formal education according to
the following table:
<BLOCKQUOTE>AA/AS Degree - 0<BR>
BS/BA Degree - 1 year<BR>
MS/MA Degree - 1.5 years<BR>
PhD - 2 years<BR>
JrD - 2 years</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A NAME="anchor360763"></A><BR>
<HR><A HREF="#anchor360763"><B>4.0</B> <B>MAINTENANCE OF CERTIFICATION</B></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>4.1 Having attained the status of &quot;CFEA&quot;, each individual
will be required to undergo recertification review every two years as specified
by requirements under the NREP - REPA certification.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><CENTER><HR><A HREF="FEAA.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="FEAAmiss.html">Mission</A><BR>
<A HREF="FEAAcert.html">Certification</A> | <A HREF="FEAApro.html">Professionalism</A><BR>
<A HREF="FEAAmem.html">Membership</A> | <A HREF="FEAAinfo.html">For Additional
Information</A></CENTER>
</BODY>
