<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY LINK="#00fd00" BGCOLOR="#ccf5cc">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Images/feaa.gif" WIDTH="258" HEIGHT="101" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"></CENTER>
<H3><CENTER>Florida Environmental Assessors <BR>
Association, Inc. (FEAA)</CENTER>
</H3>
<B><BR>
</B><HR>
<H1><CENTER>Professionalism</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER><BR>
During the past two decades, heightened awareness of environmental contamination
has created demands for accurate scientific evaluation of the resulting
problems along with a large industry to perform this work. The improvements
in standards of practice, techniques and methodologies for these evaluations
has occurred slowly, on an as needed basis, usually following regulatory
agency code development. The development of professional standards for the
performance of contamination assessment work-products has lagged behind
both the public awareness and regulatory codes.<BR>
<BR>
FEAA started in 1990 with a mission to promote the advancement of professional
qualifications for performance of ESAs for commercial real estate. The effort
includes a commitment to require minimum education achievements, related
occupational experience and competence through examination for certified
environmental site assessment professionals. FEAA provides leadership, resources
and guidance to the contamination related consultation industry by the Certified
Florida Environmental Assessor Program which combines training in related
science, standards of practice and methodologies.</CENTER>
<P><HR><BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="FEAA.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="FEAAmiss.html">Mission</A><BR>
<A HREF="FEAAcert.html">Certification</A> | <A HREF="FEAApro.html">Professionalism</A><BR>
<A HREF="FEAAmem.html">Membership</A> | <A HREF="FEAAinfo.html">For Additional
Information</A></CENTER>
</BODY>
</HTML>
