<H3><CENTER>Florida Environmental Assessors <BR>
Association, Inc. (FEAA)</CENTER>
</H3>
<P><CENTER><B><BR>
</B><HR></CENTER>
<H1><CENTER>Membership</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER><BR>
To join the Florida Environmental Assessors Association, Inc. (FEAA) please
print this form out on your printer, mark the appropriate membership category
below and send a check for the appropriate membership amount to: <BR>
<BR>
Florida Environmental Assessors Association, Inc. (FEAA)<BR>
Post Office Box 140848<BR>
Gainesville, FL 32614-0848</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Professional
Membership: <BR>
<BR>
</B>Environmental Assessment Consultants $95.00/Year<BR>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Affiliate Membership:
<BR>
<BR>
</B>Attorneys, Bankers, Real Estate Agents, <BR>
Appraisers, Etc. $75.00/Year</BLOCKQUOTE>
Please include the following information with your check: <BR>
<BR>
Name:<INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="43"> Title: <INPUT NAME="name"
TYPE="text" SIZE="27"><BR>
Organization: <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="73"><BR>
Address: <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="75"><BR>
City <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30">State<INPUT NAME="name" TYPE=
"text" SIZE="2">Zip: <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="10"><BR>
Telephone: <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30">Fax: <INPUT NAME="name"
TYPE="text" SIZE="30"></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><CENTER><BR>
<BR>
Please indicate if you would like to get involved in any of the following
FEAA's Committees by checking the appropriate box:</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"> <B>By-Laws</B><BR>
<BR>
The By-Laws Committee is responsible for maintaining the FEAA By-Laws and
making sure the are current with current management practices.<BR>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Conference</B><BR>
<BR>
The Conference Committee is responsible for all aspects of planning the
annual conference and special conference-programs, speaker selection, location,
events, socials, exhibitions, sponsorships, entertainment <BR>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Government Relations/Ethics</B><BR>
<BR>
The Government Relations/Ethics Committee is responsible for keeping the
FEAA membership informed of legislation which may have the potential to
impact the environmental site assessment community. The Committee is also
responsible for developing and maintaining a Code of Ethics for the Association.<BR>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Membership</B><BR>
<BR>
The Membership Committee has several responsibilities, including working
to retain membership as well as recruit new members, develop a membership
directory, and conduct a survey of FEAA member needs.<BR>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Standards of
Practice:</B><BR>
<BR>
The Standards of Practice Committee is responsible for developing standards
and methodologies for the performance of activities as the relate to the
professional assessment of potential environmental problems associated with
commercial real estate.<BR>
<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox"><B>Qualification
&amp; Education:</B><BR>
<BR>
The Qualification &amp; Education Committee is responsible for putting together
the CFEA Training Course,. This includes developing the CFEA course curriculum,
examination questions, and developing qualification criteria for individuals
that may take for the CFEA exam.</BLOCKQUOTE>
