  <TITLE>About SWIX</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="TAN.GIF">

<P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER="0" WIDTH="600" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING=
"0" HEIGHT="116">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="111"><IMG SRC="SWIX2.GIF" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="72" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="285"><H2 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#00BA00">The Southern Waste Information Exchange
(SWIX)</FONT></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><I>A Service of <BR>
Keep Florida Beautiful, Inc.</I></TD>
<TD WIDTH="175"><IMG SRC="KFB2.GIF" WIDTH="163" HEIGHT="99" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <TABLE BORDER="0" WIDTH="600" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="2"><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>What is the Southern Waste Information eXchange (SWIX)?</H2>
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="150"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="350"><P>The Southern Waste Information eXchange (SWIX), a service of the Keep
Florida Beautiful, Inc., is a non-profit clearinghouse and repository for
industry concerning information on:</P>

<UL>
  <LI>market development,
  <LI>recycled products,
  <LI>solid and hazardous waste management;
  <LI>current regulations/legislation;
  <LI>alternative and emerging waste management technologies;
  <LI>trade journals and associations;
  <LI>technical reports;
  <LI>the availability of and demand for waste materials; and
  <LI>waste management services and products.
</UL>
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="2"><P><A NAME="catalog"></A></P>

<H2><font color=#228b22">
The SWIX Catalog</FONT></H2></a></td></tr>

<tr><td width=150><br></td>
<td width=350><dd>The SWIX Catalog is a publication that is designed to assist
industry in 
the area of solid and hazardous waste management.  The Catalog
provides 
information concerning the availability of and demand for waste
materials as 
well as providing information related to waste management services
and 
products. 
<P>
<dd>The SWIX Catalog is published three times a year (April, August
and December).  
<P>
<dd>The Catalog is divided into three sections: 
<a href="matavil.html">Materials Available</a>,
<a href="matwant.html">Materials Wanted</a> and a 
<a href="wastes.html">Waste Management Services</a> section.  
<P>
<P><dd>Code numbers have been assigned to each Material Available and
Material Wanted Listing for confidentiality reasons. <P> 


</td></tr>

<tr><td colspan=2>
<a name="subscribe"><H2><font color=#228b22">Subscriptions</FONT></H2>
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="150"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="350"><P><dd>To obtain a subscription to the hardcopy of the SWIX Catalog send
a check for $15 to:</P>

<P><I>The Southern Waste Information Exchange (SWIX) <BR>
A Service of Keep Florida Beautiful, Inc. <BR>
Post Office Box 960 <BR>
Tallahassee, Florida 32302</I></P>

<P><dd>Because the SWIX program is in part sponsored by the State of Florida,
there is not a fee to subscribe to the hardcopy of the SWIX Catalog for
Florida based businesses or governmental agencies.</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="2"><P><A NAME="fees"></A></P>

<H2><font color=#228b22">Fees</FONT></h2></a></td></tr>
<tr><td width=150><br></td><td width=350>
<dd>
There is not a fee to list a Material Wanted Listing in the SWIX
Catalog.  A 
$75 charge per  listing is assessed to each Material Available
and Waste 
Management Service Listing.  Because the SWIX program is in part
sponsored 
by the State of Florida, there is not a fee to list a Material
Available Listing for 
Florida based business or governmental agencies. <P>
</td></tr>



<tr><td colspan=2><P><a name="disclaimer">
<H2><font color=#228b22">Disclaimer</FONT></H2>
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="150"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="350"><dd>Information provided through the SWIX Catalog is supplied by the listing
company. Neither KFB, sponsors, nor any advisoror member thereof is liable
for any information, error, representation, or makes any warranty, expressed
or implied as to the accuracy of the material, service, or product/equipment
offered through the SWIX catalog. KFB is not responsible for the determination
of what may constitute a hazardous substance or create a hazardous situation.
Mention of trade names or commercial products does not constitute endorsement
or recommendation for use. KFB does not make judgments with respect to any
legal requirements, particularly for the storage, transportation, treatment,
or disposal of what may be defined as hazardous substances or hazardous
waste. KFB reserves the right not to list a material, delist a material,
or edit information provided by the listing company.</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;</P>

