<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>How to place a SWIX listing</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="TAN.GIF">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER="0" WIDTH="600" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING=
"0" HEIGHT="116">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="111"><IMG SRC="SWIX2.GIF" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="72" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="285"><H2 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#00BA00">The Southern Waste Information Exchange
(SWIX)</FONT></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><I>A Service of <BR>
Keep Florida Beautiful, Inc.</I></TD>
<TD WIDTH="175"><IMG SRC="KFB2.GIF" WIDTH="163" HEIGHT="99" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;</H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES </FONT></H1>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><I><FONT COLOR="#000000">How to place a<BR>
Waste Management Service listing<BR>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=-1>* = New Listing</FONT></I><FONT COLOR="#000000"
 SIZE=-1> </FONT></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>I. Recycling<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Bag Recycling</B> <B>SW:S01-0347 </B></P>

<P>Bulk bag recycling service. We will contract clean (wash or air blow
out) your bags, inspect them, prepare them for reuse and return them to
you at a price lower than new bags. We will need a sample for testing, MSDS,
and information on quantity. Contact: James T. Gleeson, The Olde Bag Company,
Inc., Post Office box 860, Tucker, GA 30085-0860. Telephone: (770) 939-4049.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Oils, Solvents and Industrial Wastes SW:S01-0222 </B></P>

<P>We can provide the packaging services, transportation, and recycling
or waste exchange of oils, solvents, and a variety of industrial wastes.
Cradle-to-Grave management and documentation provided. Contact: Mr. Robert
O. Kincart, American Compliance Technologies, 1875 West Main Street, American
Way &amp; State Road 60 West, Bartow, FL 33830, Telephone: (941) 533-2000.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Organic/Inorganic Chemicals SW:S01-0282 </B></P>

<P>Contact us first before expensive disposal of usable chemicals. We use
all types of organic and inorganic chemicals. Drums, bags or bulk. Serving
the U.S. TX. Contact: Mr. Elton Dornbush, Expo Chemical Co., 12602 Manorwood,
Cypress, TX 77429, Telephone (713) 890-4553.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Recycling SW:S01-0266 </B></P>

<P>Buys many unused items for reuse that would otherwise be dumped; such
as chemicals, freons/genesolv, ion exchange resins, kevlar fabrics, epoxy,
RTV, silicones, pigments/dyes, plastics, catalysts, reagents, raw-materials,
electronic chemicals, metallic oxides, oils, siloxane, and all related unused
materials. Contact: Mr. David Tress, Kemstar Corporation, 3456 Wade Street,
Los Angeles, CA 90066, Telephone: (310) 390-0180, Fax: (310) 391-8143 or
on the East coast call (914) 681-0126.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Waste Recycling SW:S01-0331 </B></P>

<P>Comply with waste minimization by turning your waste into secondary fuels
for the cement industry. We provide complete service for the legal disposal
of hazardous and non-hazardous wastes with competitive pricing. Liquids
or solids, drums and bulk accepted. In some cases we will pay for your waste.
Recycling options available for qualified streams. Contact: Mr. James Lederer,
ECA, Inc. Post Office Box 1288, Highlands City, FL 33846, Telephone: (800)
327-3634, FAX: (813) 648-0337.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>II. Equipment and Supplies<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Composite Molding System SW:S02-0348 </B></P>

<P>Turn your waste material into a profitable asset. Sorbilite, Inc. manufactures
a composite molding system that turns your fibrous waste or plastic into
marketable products. Contact: Mr. Deanne Beckwith, Sorbilite, Inc., 5721
Bayside Road, Virginia Beach, VA 23455, Telephone: (804) 464-3564.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Containers SW:S02-0346 </B></P>

<P>Duval Container Co. is a distributor of glass, plastic, fibre and steel
containers such as bottle, jars, pails and drums. UN Certified containers
are available. Contact: Joe Thornhill, Duval Container Co., 91 S. Myrtle
Avenue, Jacksonville, FL 32203, Telephone: (904) 355-6591.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Environmental Compliance Products SW:S02-0223 </B></P>

<P>Sorbent products for oil and solvent clean-up, hazardous material storage
buildings, overpack/salvage drums, all types of DOT approved containers
(metal and poly), and spill response equipment. Our new &quot;FACT PACK&quot;
(First Action Contingency Tackle) is designed to assist small quantity generators
comply with current state and federal requirements for spill clean-up. Contact:
Robert O. Kincart, American Compliance Technologies, Inc., 1875 West Main
Street, American Way &amp; State Road 60 West, Bartow, FL 33830, Telephone:
(941) 533-2000.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>III. Environmental Consulting<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Professional Consulting &amp; Engineering Management
Services SW:S03-0340 </B></P>

<P>Responsive environmental consulting and engineering management services
in the areas of USTs, ESAs, Contamination Assessment, Remedial Design and
Implementation, RCRA, Compliance, Permitting, and Litigation. Contact: Mark
Napolitan, P.E., Apex Environmanagement, Inc. 7517 S.E. Marsh Fern Lane,
Hobe Sound, FL 33455. Telephone: (407) 220-0056.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>IV. Legal and Health - Related Services<HR></H2>

<P>No listings at this time.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>V. Tank Management<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Tank Removal and Cleaning SW:S05-0224 </B></P>

<P>Florida SUPER ACT contractor (FL license # PTC 000593). Chemical, solvent,
and petroleum tank removal, abandonment and cleaning services available.
Excavation and reclamation of contaminated land. All procedures performed
in compliance with local, state, and federal regulations. Southern U.S.
Contact: Mr. Robert O. Kincart, American Compliance Technologies, 1875 West
Main Street, American Way &amp; State Road 60 West, Bartow, FL 33830, Telephone:
(941) 533-2000.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>VI. Collection and Transportation<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Transportation SW:S06-0225 </B></P>

<P>Collection and transportation of hazardous wastes for disposal, recycling,
or treatment to EPA permitted facilities. Can handle bulk or drum quantities.
Complete waste management services. Cradle-to-Grave management. Contact:
Mr. Robert O. Kincart, American Compliance Technologies, 1875 West Main
Street, American Way &amp; State Road 60 West, Bartow, FL 33830, Telephone:
(941) 533-2000.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>VII. Storage, Treatment, Disposal<HR></H2>

<P>No listings at this time.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>VII. Emergency Response / Clean-Up<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Emergency Response SW:S08-0345 </B></P>

<P>Emergency response and clean-up services. Contact: Robert O. Kincart,
American Compliance Technologies, Inc., <BR>
1875 West Main Street, American Way &amp; State Road 60 West, Bartow, FL
33830, Telephone: (941) 533- 2000.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>IX. Laboratory Analysis<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Independent Laboratory Testing SW:S09-0344 </B></P>

<P>EPA Certified analysis of wastes (TCLP), paint filters, sludges, incinerator
ash, biosolids, metals, mercury, soil contamination, and well monitoring.
Accuracy and service since 1922. Contact: Mr. Wes Tyler, Thornton Laboratories,
Inc., 1145 E. Cass Street, Tampa, FL 33602, Telephone: (813) 223-9702.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>X. Waste Minimization<HR></H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>On-site Treatment Services SW:S10-0339 </B></P>

<P>Contact: Mr. Robert Picek, Lomar Reclamation Services, 2845-D Broce,
Norman, OK 73072, Telephone: (800) 299-3456.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>XI. Miscellaneous<HR></H2>

<P>No listings at this time.</P>

