<P><A NAME="anchor411145"></A><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR>
<A HREF="../index.html">Return to today's headlines</A><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H3><A HREF="#anchor411145">New law firm director specializes in enviro
law</A></H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>FORT LAUDERDALE -- (EnviroWorld) -- Daniel Taylor has been named a director
  of the law firm of Tripp, Scott, Conklin &amp; Smith. He has more than
  25 years of litigation experience and previously was assistant Broward
  County Attorney serving as chief of the Environmental Law Section. Taylor
  will focus on land use and environmental law.</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

