ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<HR></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="ECOTOURS.html">Interested in Florida EcoTours?</A></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><HR></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Florida's Growing EcoTour Industry Could Spur Enviro Consulting</H3>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><I>by Patricia Ashton</I></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><FONT COLOR="#006600">COULD ECOTOURISM BE A NEW</FONT> economic savior
  for Florida counties and the new market for environmental consultants?</P>
  <P>Ecotourism summits, conferences and committees are springing up all
  over Florida. Long on theory and short on practical solutions seems to
  be the attitude of  many attendees. Since creative and hopefully practical
  solutions remain the domain of the consulting world, perhaps there is a
  market for firms suffering from the atmosphere of deregulation and non-enforcement.
  </P>
  <P>So what are the secrets to this ecotourism industry and why is it intermeshed
  with sustainable development philosophy?</P>
  <P><B>A mega market</B></P>
  <P>Ecotourism is considered the fastest growing market in the tourism industry,
  according to the World Tourism Organization with an annual growth rate
  of 5% worldwide and representing 6% of the world gross domestic product,
  11.4% of all consumer spending - not a market to be taken lightly, particularly
  in Florida where tourism is the number one industry generating more than
  32 billion dollars in annual revenues. </P>
  <P>It is not surprising that consultants have joined counties in recognizing
  the potential of this developing industry. The rise of this niche market
  and its role in promoting the principles of sustainable development world
  wide was a topic addressed by Megan Epler Wood, Executive Director of The
  Ecotourism Society at the Dade County Ecotourism Conference this September
  when ecotourism experts from across the country met in what some pointed
  out as Florida's least likely ecotourism destination.</P>
  <P>The closing tone of the conference left an audience more knowledgeable
  about sustainable development successes in the Virgin Islands and the Ozarks
  and with information on the planning strategies and capabilities available
  from the consultants specializing in sustainable tourism and natural resources
  development. </P>
  <P><FONT COLOR="#006600">Florida market just developing</FONT></P>
  <P>Painfully obvious was the lack of current successful examples of  sustainable
  tourism developments within south Florida though two promising &quot;eco&quot;
  models were revealed. </P>
  <P>One such example is called Eco-Camps of America . A private-public partnership
  model project, Eco-Camps of America, created by C. Wendall Collins plans
  sustainable facilities and infrastructure specifically for the ecotourism
  market. The conference, as with many of the projects,  represented the
  efforts of &quot;environmental consultants&quot; turned &quot;ecotourism
  consultants&quot;.</P>
  <P>&nbsp;</P>
  <P><I>&quot;Ecotourism ...is any tourism planned and carried out in an
  environmentally sound and sustainable manner&quot; (R.E. Ashton, Jr. 1989)</I></P>
  <P>&nbsp;</P>
  <P><FONT COLOR="#006600">Palm Beach on the move</FONT></P>
  <P>On the heels of this conference, the Palm Beach County Ecotourism Summit
  (also arranged by and the program planning assisted by environmental/ecotourism
  consultants) met at the Omni in West Palm Beach on October 31  to examine
  the implications and opportunities ecotourism offers for tourism and related
  industries in that county. </P>
  <P>With the theme, &quot;Discover the Nature of Palm Beach County&quot;
  this conference was approached from the standpoint of involvement by the
  traditional tourism industry, largely focused on hotels and attractions,
  in the developing ecotourism market. The ecotourist market was profiled
  and a marketing session on how to reach that market included in the day's
  activities.</P>
  <P>Participants brought up their successes using the WWW for reaching potential
  visitors and for receiving reservations. EcoTour World and its related
  site EcoTour Florida, the new Eco Travel and Information Planning Center
  website was introduced as a new market tool for reaching this sophisticated
  and discriminating market of ecotourists. </P>
  <P>This interactive website utilizes a vast storehouse of information (obtained
  by consultants) and unique ecotourism &quot;best eco-travel&quot; recommendations
  by experts not available on any other site. </P>
  <P><B>Tallahassee discovers nature</B></P>
  <P>The increasing participation of exhibitors, participants and speakers
  in these and the many other such conferences is indicative of the importance
  of this new market. </P>
  <P>Tallahassee has not overlooked its importance, creating an eco-tourism
  advisory committee following the September meeting in Orlando of the Governor's
  Conference on Tourism. </P>
  <P>The Florida Game and Freshwater Fish Commission launched their involvement
  in sustainable tourism with a Watchable Wildlife Conference and Department
  of Environmental Protection Division of Recreation and Parks has had a
  visible presence at all conferences.</P>
  <P><B>Calling all consultants?</B></P>
  <P>What can this mean for environmental consulting firms? A new market
  not dependent upon the presence or enforcement of environmental regulation
  that requires similar skills. </P>
  <P>Ecotourism or sustainable tourism development places the need for environmental
  conservation and  habitat management on an economic need basis not on regulation.
  Without long term monitoring and management plans to provide continued
  protection for the resources upon which ecotourism development depends
  the industry will collapse. These are skills environmental firms have in
  abundance.</P>
  <P>To successfully implement work in the sustainable tourism industry,
  consultants also need staff with an intimate knowledge of the workings
  of inbound tour operators, outbound tour operators, and the needs of the
  ecotourist and the ecotourism market. </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

