<H1><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Images/image24.gif" WIDTH="293" HEIGHT="84" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
Environmental Professional Resources-Listservs</CENTER>
</H1>
<HR>
<H3></H3>
<I>(Reprinted with the permission of the Society of Environmental Journalists)</I>
<H3>Listserv? What's a Listserv?</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>A listserv is a type of software. But more to the point, it's
one of several related types of software used to operate Internet mailing
lists. These lists allow you to participate in e-mail discussions of wide-ranging
topics, including journalism and the environment. <BR>
<BR>
If you follow the instructions and send e-mail to any of the addresses below,
you'll soon receive a note welcoming you to the list and telling you how
to post messages and how to cancel your subscription -- which can be a good
thing to know, since some of these lists produce as many as 50 messages
per day. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<EM>Finally, a special note for overly literal readers:</EM> In the &quot;To
join&quot; instructions below, substitute your first name for &quot;yourfirstname,&quot;
your last name for &quot;yourlastname,&quot; and your E-mail address for
&quot;yourE-mailaddress.&quot; We know, it's confusing. That's life. </BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<HR><A NAME="environmental"></A>
<H3>Environmental lists</H3>
<DL>
  <DT><STRONG>AESP-net </STRONG>
  <DD>Association of Energy Service Professionals <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:majordomo@dnai.com"> majordomo@dnai.com</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe AESP-net</EM> in the body of your e-mail message and
nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Aeroso-l </STRONG>
  <DD>Health Effects of Particulate Matter (Air Pollution). <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@nic.surfnet.nl"> listserv@nic.surfnet.nl</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Aeroso-l yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body
of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Aquifer </STRONG>
  <DD>Pollution and Groundwater Discharge. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@IBACSATA.BITNET"> listserv@ibacsata.bitnet</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Aquifer yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body of
your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Aqua-L </STRONG>
  <DD>Discussions on the science, technologies and business of aquaculture.
<BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@VM.UOGUELPH.CA"> listserv@vm.uoguelph.ca</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Aqua-L yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body of
your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Audubon </STRONG>
  <DD>Discussions of the National Audubon Society (U.S.). <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:AutoShare@rip.physics.unk.edu">
AutoShare@rip.physics.unk.edu</A></EM> with <EM>subscribe Audubon yourfirstname
yourlastname</EM> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the
&quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Bay-Delta Forum </STRONG>
  <DD>California water, focusing on the San Francisco Bay-Delta estuary.
<BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:bay-delta-forum-request@sacto.mp.usbr.gov">
bay-delta-forum-request@sacto.mp.usbr.gov</A></EM> with <EM>subscribe</EM>
in both the subject line and the body of your e-mail message. 
  <DT><STRONG>Ca-water </STRONG>
  <DD>California water issues. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:majordomo@list.dcn.davis.ca.us">
majordomo@list.dcn.davis.ca.us</A></EM> with <EM>subscribe ca-water</EM>
in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot;
line. 
  <DT><STRONG>CoastGIS </STRONG>
  <DD>Coastal geographic information systems distribution list. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@IRLEARN.UCD.IE"> listserv@irlearn.ucd.ie</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe CoastGIS yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body
of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Coastnet </STRONG>
  <DD>A forum for planners, managers, researchers and others to discuss
national and international coastal management issues. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@URIACC.URI.EDU"> listserv@uriacc.uri.edu</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Coastnet yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body
of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Conslink </STRONG>
  <DD>An electronic conference and bulletin board to improve communication
among individuals and institutions around the world who are interested in
biological conservation. Sponsored by the Smithsonian Institution. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@SIVM.SI.EDU"> listserv@sivm.si.edu</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Conslink yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body
of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Contract-debate </STRONG>
  <DD>A spin-off of the &quot;Contract-Env&quot; list (see below). This
list is solely for debate about environmental issues, environmental politics,
and their associated issues. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:listserv@netcom.com"> listserv@netcom.com</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe contract-debate</EM> in the body of your e-mail message
and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Contract-env </STRONG>
  <DD>A moderated e-mail list intended to foster discussion and vitriol
on the ramifications of the &quot;Contract for America&quot; for the environment.
All substantive environmental subjects are fair game, as are the political
and policy issues that relate to them. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:listserv@netcom.com"> listserv@netcom.com</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe contract-env</EM> in the body of your e-mail message
and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Cturtle </STRONG>
  <DD>Sea Turtle Biology and Conservation. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@NERVM.NERDC.UFL.EDU">
listserv@nervm.nerdc.ufl.edu</A></EM> with <EM>subscribe Cturtle yourfirstname
yourlastname</EM> in the body of your e-mail message and nothing in the
&quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Deepsea </STRONG>
  <DD>Serves the global community of deep-sea and hydrothermal vent and
seep biologists working in the areas of evolution, ecology, biogeography,
paleontology, systematics, phylogenetics, population genetics and zoology.
<BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@UVVM.UVIC.CA"> listserv@uvvm.uvic.ca</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Deepsea yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body of
your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Eco-curriculum </STRONG>
  <DD>Discussion of environmental education on the Internet, including the
use of tools like e-mail, gopher, networked virtual realities (NVR's), the
World Wide Web, and other new means to teach an environmental curriculum.
<BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:listproc@envirolink.org"> listproc@envirolink.org</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Eco-curriculum yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the
body of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line.
  <DT><STRONG>Ecolog-L</STRONG>
  <DD>For information of interest to <A HREF="http://www.sdsc.edu/1/SDSC/Research/Comp_Bio/ESA/ESA.html">Ecological
Society of America </A>members, such as job listings, funding opportunities,
and ESA news. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:LISTSERV@UMDD.UMD.EDU"> listserv@umdd.umd.edu</A></EM>
with <EM>subscribe Ecolog-L yourfirstname yourlastname</EM> in the body
of your e-mail message and nothing in the &quot;Subject:&quot; line. 
  <DT><STRONG>Ecology </STRONG>
  <DD>Discussion of the interaction of ecology and politics. <BR>
To join, send e-mail to:<EM><A HREF="mailto:majordomo@bluemarble.net"> majordomo@bluemarble.net</A></EM>
